commentBody:
@Lori 

That’s what I had at first, even though it seemed unlikely.

That word always reminds me of the anagrammed sign in the title sequence for “Fawlty Towers.”

@Clare 
Hear hear.
I too strive to remain polite and courteous. Whatever we may feel about a crossword, we should applaud the work that has gone into it. Occasionally I do come across a clue/answer that really triggers me, but it’s rare and I hope I make my complaint reasonable and not whiney /aggressive.  It’s only a game after all.

@Théo 

Yesterday, I did a 2006 puzzle with the clue “Georges Perec's 1969 novel "La Disparition" is written entirely without this”: AN E. 

I knew the answer ought to be something like “The letter E,” but since that didn’t fit, I left that blank a while. (The actual answer seems a bit off to me. Maybe it would have been better clued as “What Georges Perec's 1969 novel "La Disparition" does not contain”?)

@Lewis 

Thanks for the reference to the 3/13/20 puzzle. I glanced at it quickly and saw how lovely it was—quickly closed it to avoid seeing the answers, and went to the archives. I've been working through 2023 (I only started in August of '23) but I'll do that one next, instead!

:-)

@CCNY 
It is powdered....just add water, if you favor spending money for and drinking particulate matter ....

These days if I have TEA, it's herbal.  But mostly I just go with filtered water from the fridge.

